			<!--
        PERSONNAL NOTE : It's more efficient (from my point of view) to use <picture> and <source> tags
        than only <img> with "srcset" attribute.
        As written here :  https://slides.com/welcomattic/des-images-au-cordeau-pour-vos-applications-symfony#/38
        With <picture> and <source>, the media query is always read by the browser, whereas with <img> and "srcset",
        sometimes it's not. So, i personnaly prefer using <picture> and <source> tags.
        Both are written here for test purpose.

        Other sources of information about this :
        - http://w3c.github.io/html/semantics-embedded-content.html#viewport-based-selection
        - https://www.alsacreations.com/article/lire/1621-responsive-images-srcset.html
